<p>Reports unquoted port mappings in Docker Compose files.</p>
<p>
  According to the <a href="https://docs.docker.com/compose/compose-file/compose-file-v3/#short-syntax-1">Compose file specification</a>,
  mapping ports in the <code>HOST:CONTAINER</code> format may lead to erroneous results when using a container port lower than 60,
  because YAML parses numbers in the format <code>xx:yy</code> as a base-60 value.
  For this reason, we recommend always explicitly specifying the port mappings as strings.
</p>
<p><b>Examples:</b></p>
<pre><code>
  ports:
    - 3000
    - 3000-3005
    - 22:22
    - 8080:8080
</code></pre>
<p>After the quick-fix is applied:</p>
<pre><code>
  ports:
    - "3000"
    - "3000-3005"
    - "22:22"
    - "8080:8080"
</code></pre>
</body>
